---
source: kcl-lib/src/simulation_tests.rs
description: Result of unparsing mbd_name_using_face_id.kcl
---
// Tests `mbd::name` with faces and edges identified by the index-based
// helpers `faceId` and `edgeId`. These helpers are how callers refer to
// geometry that can't be tagged directly (e.g. imported STEP files or
// operations that don't yet support tagging their outputs).

@settings(kclVersion = 2.0)

cylinder = startSketchOn(XY)
  |> circle(center = [0, 0], radius = 4.09)
  |> extrude(length = 5)

// `faceId` returns a `TaggedFace`. `mbd::name` resolves it to the face's
// engine UUID via the adjacent-face lookup, the same as for sketch-tag
// faces.
mbd::name(face = faceId(cylinder, index = 2), name = "top_face_via_faceId")

// `edgeId` returns an `Edge` (a UUID). `mbd::name` uses it directly.
mbd::name(edge = edgeId(cylinder, index = 2), name = "top_edge_via_edgeId")
